					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This records the allotment (by the temple authorities) out of the <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> land at Tiruvalandurainallūr, of 1(1/2) <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold, 3 <hi rend="italic">kaḻam</hi> of paddy and a pair of cloths, as remuneration to a <hi rend="italic">śākkai</hi> of Adalaiyūr for <hi rend="bold">enacting 3 parts of a śākkai-kūttu (dance-dramas ?)</hi> in the temple on the day of a festival occurring in Aśvini asterism in Aippigai month. This <hi rend="italic">śākkai-kūttu</hi> is mentioned in other inscriptions also (vide <hi rend="bold">M.E.R.</hi> for 1915, Part II. para. 22).</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
